{
  "_comment": "DockBack custom seccomp allow-list for the app container (PLAN §10.3, Security.md §2). It is an explicit allow-list (defaultAction SCMP_ACT_ERRNO): any syscall not listed returns EPERM. It is STRICTLY TIGHTER than Docker's default profile — it omits every capability-gated syscall (already denied by cap_drop: ALL) and additionally denies dangerous non-privileged calls this static Go/net/SQLite server never makes: ptrace, process_vm_readv/writev, personality, userfaultfd, perf_event_open, kcmp, add_key/keyctl, setns/unshare, mount family, module/kexec/reboot, and clock/time setters. The allow-list covers exactly what the Go 1.26 runtime, net poller, pure-Go SQLite (file I/O), argon2/zstd (memory), and TLS need. Applied only to the fully-hardened app container; the socket-proxy keeps its default profile. Opt-out by removing the seccomp security_opt line.",
  "defaultAction": "SCMP_ACT_ERRNO",
  "defaultErrnoRet": 1,
  "archMap": [
    {
      "architecture": "SCMP_ARCH_X86_64",
      "subArchitectures": ["SCMP_ARCH_X86", "SCMP_ARCH_X32"]
    },
    {
      "architecture": "SCMP_ARCH_AARCH64",
      "subArchitectures": ["SCMP_ARCH_ARM"]
    }
  ],
